## 3/15/17 ##
How code is therapy: good, bad and ugly.

3pm.
I'm not gonna lie. I am feeling miserable and am in tears throughout the day and at home. The gender imbalance it starting to get to me. There is a playful competitiveness to our class but nonetheless less it feel competitive and it sucks to be the slow kid. That's me in 201.

Besides that I am really struggling with the overall pace. Last night I got home at 10:30p. I read till 12am and still didn't complete the reading. Class feels very fast, screens code, browser flash in front of me and I am unable to keep up.

#Suggestion#
Nick, during class can you try to console/browser and code as a split screen vs. overlaying them + toggling between screens? I am trying to understand code and poof, the code is gone and I am looking at a browser forgetting the code entirely. I want to be able to compare code to browser/console during the code review.

6pm.
# Today I learned #
It is very cool how I can use JS to manipulate an HTML file. Even though it is hard I really like the Salmon Cake project. It is amazing how many commands there are for JS and I really want to learn it. I like how the entire package HTML/CSS/JS works together. I think I'll stay here for awhile.

I also did a few things on git and I did it right! Then I followed some advice and that was wrong. So now I know 1. I get it and 2. I am not the online that is getting things wrong.

10:15pm
Hadiya was right. I have a self confidence problem. AND I have been getting lost in my crappy self talk. Agh. How did code end up being a therapy session?

AGGGGHHHHHHHH!!!!!!!!
Me.



























